OL,3,CThings really do seem better in the
OL,4,Cmorning, scientists say
OL,6,FPeople often tell their loved ones
OL,7,F"everything will be better in the
OL,8,Fmorning", and now scientists have
OL,9,Fshown this is likely to be true.
OL,11,FA large study found the mornings are
OL,12,Foften the time of day people are at
OL,13,Ftheir best and report the greatest
OL,14,Ffeelings of wellbeing.
OL,16,FThe research also reinforced what
OL,17,Fpeople often believe to be true ` that
OL,18,Fthe summer months make people feel
OL,19,Fhappier than the winter ones.
