OL,3,CThings really do seem better in the
OL,4,Cmorning, scientists say
OL,6,FExperts analysed data from 49,218
OL,7,Fadults drawn from the University
OL,8,FCollege London (UCL) Covid-19 Social
OL,9,FStudy, which followed people for two
OL,10,Fyears from March 2020 to March 2022.
OL,12,FThe findings showed that people
OL,13,Fgenerally woke up "feeling best" but,
OL,14,Fby midnight, they were "feeling worst".
OL,16,FResearchers added: "There is also an
OL,17,Fassociation with day of the week and
OL,18,Fseason, with particularly strong
OL,19,Fevidence for better mental health and
OL,20,Fwellbeing in the summer."
