OL,3,CThings really do seem better in the
OL,4,Cmorning, scientists say
OL,6,FThe results showed that happiness,
OL,7,Flife satisfaction, and worthwhile
OL,8,Fratings were all higher on Mondays and
OL,9,FFridays than on Sundays, and happiness
OL,10,Fwas also higher on Tuesdays.
OL,12,FBut there was no evidence that
OL,13,Floneliness differed across days of the
OL,14,Fweek.
OL,16,FThe researchers also suggested that
OL,17,Fchanges in mental health and wellbeing
OL,18,Facross the day might be explained by
OL,19,Fphysiological changes associated with
OL,20,Fthe body clock.
