OL,3,CThings really do seem better in the
OL,4,Cmorning, scientists say
OL,6,F"For example, cortisol (a hormone that
OL,7,Fregulates mood, motivation and fear)
OL,8,Fpeaks shortly after waking and reaches
OL,9,Fits lowest levels around bedtime,"
OL,10,Fthey said.
OL,12,FHowever, they said the differences
OL,13,Fnoted between weekdays and weekends
OL,14,Fmay be driven by things such as the
OL,15,Fsequence of daily activities, which
OL,16,Fare likely to be different between
OL,17,Fweekends and weekdays.
